# Release SOC Compliance Tracker – Phase 4
## Kubernetes Deployment Readiness & Environment Validation

## Objective

This phase aims to automate Deployment Readiness validation by integrating with Kubernetes. The objective is to identify which release branch is currently deployed in the IST and Stage environments, validate whether the correct Fix Version has been deployed, store the deployment metadata in the database, and present the results in the Release Readiness dashboard.

Please first analyze the existing project structure and reuse the current architecture, coding patterns, services, repositories, DTOs, controllers, React components, and APIs wherever possible. Avoid duplicate implementations and keep the solution modular, configurable, secure, and production-ready.

---

# Business Requirement

Currently, before every release, the Integration Testing (IST) team manually verifies whether the correct release branch has been deployed into their Kubernetes environment.

The verification includes:

- Identifying the active deployment.
- Determining which GitHub branch is deployed.
- Verifying the deployment timestamp.
- Identifying the Git commit deployed.
- Ensuring the deployed branch matches the selected Fix Version.

This entire process should now be automated.

Initially, the solution should support the IST/Test environment and Stage environment. The architecture should also be future-ready for Production.

